questions.answer:
While loop checks condition before executing the loop body, so it may execute zero times. Do-while loop executes the body once before checking condition, so it always executes at least once.

Example:
```c
// while loop
int i = 5;
while(i < 5) {
    printf("Executed"); // Won't execute
}

// do-while loop
int i = 5;
do {
    printf("Executed"); // Executes once
} while(i < 5);
```

